            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-23014" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Integrated Studies in Ed (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/608">Faculty of Education</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Curriculum and Instruction              : This course examines the organization of education in Quebec from various perspectives, including historical, political, social and legal. It aims to provide students with sufficient knowledge that they can begin the life-long learning process of a professional educator, aware of, and contributing to, the policy talk on school.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

